2026-05-08 13:57:53 INFO     [static_analyzer.reference_resolve_mixin:20] Fixing source code reference lines for the analysis: # Abstract Components Overview
**Component:** `Ingestion & OCR Engine`
   - *Description*: Responsible for preparing raw images and extracting raw text data. It handles computer vision enhancements (deskewing, normalization) and abstracts multiple OCR backends (Paddle, Tesseract, etc.) behind a unified interface with a filesystem-based cache to optimize performance.
   - *Source Group Names*: Image Pre-processing & Enhancement, OCR Abstraction & Engine Layer
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`preProcess.process_image` FileRef: `preProcess.py``, `QName:`ocr_engine.ocr_with_cache` FileRef: `ocr_engine.py``, `QName:`batch.get_ocr_engine` FileRef: `batch.py``
**Component:** `Spatial & Semantic Parser`
   - *Description*: The core transformation engine that converts unstructured OCR bounding boxes into structured receipt objects. It uses geometric algorithms to reconstruct rows and columns, and integrates LLM logic (Claude API) to handle complex layouts or ambiguous text extraction.
   - *Source Group Names*: Spatial Parser & LLM Extraction
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`parser.Receipt` FileRef: `parser.py``, `QName:`parser.group_into_rows` FileRef: `parser.py``, `QName:`llm_parser.parse_with_llm` FileRef: `llm_parser.py``
**Component:** `Pipeline Controller`
   - *Description*: Orchestrates the end-to-end execution flow. It manages the lifecycle of a processing job, including loading business rules (TOML), triggering the parser, and applying categorization logic to map receipt items to specific accounts.
   - *Source Group Names*: Business Logic & Pipeline Orchestration
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`batch.process_receipt` FileRef: `batch.py``, `QName:`rules.load_rules` FileRef: `rules.py``, `QName:`batch.categorize_items` FileRef: `batch.py``
**Component:** `Accounting Exporter`
   - *Description*: The "Load" phase of the ETL. It translates structured data into final financial artifacts, specifically Excel spreadsheets and hledger journals. It includes reconciliation logic to match new receipts against existing bank or ledger entries.
   - *Source Group Names*: Exporters & Accounting Integration
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`update_excel.update_excel` FileRef: `update_excel.py``, `QName:`update_excel.find_excel_match` FileRef: `update_excel.py``, `QName:`update_journal.main` FileRef: `update_journal.py``
**Component:** `Quality Assurance & Calibration`
   - *Description*: Manages the system's reliability and evolution. It tracks processed state to prevent duplicates, runs regression snapshots to ensure parser changes don't break existing logic, and provides tools for fine-tuning OCR models (TrOCR) and correction tables.
   - *Source Group Names*: State Management & Regression Testing, Model Training & Calibration Tools
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`processed.is_processed` FileRef: `processed.py``, `QName:`snapshots.run_regression` FileRef: `snapshots.py``, `QName:`train_trocr.train` FileRef: `train_trocr.py``(Ingestion & OCR Engine, sends raw text detections and bounding box coordinates to, Spatial & Semantic Parser)
